@AmberWilkie thank you very much, I can confirm your solution worked for me. You saved my code from being thrown in the trash.

I had to slightly amend the solution because my setup is different (it's a serverless function where a template is downloaded from Azure blob storage and then the new workbook is again saved on Azure blob storage) and so my specific problem was that I was initializing my blob storage query after committing the workbook, it feels counter intuitive to do it before the stream has ended but it works!

For anyone that comes accross this issue, I highly recommend @AmberWilkie 's guide
